text:
She's been single for nearly two months.

But Nikki Bella revealed on Sunday's episode of Total Bellas that she's confused by her ex-fiance John Cena's recent media pleas for a reconciliation.

The 34-year-old wrestler chatted with twin sister Brie about Cena's recent public appearances and her conflicting feelings about their relationship.

Complex: Nikki Bella revealed on Sunday's episode of Total Bellas that she's confused by her ex-fiance John Cena's recent media pleas for a reconciliation

'It's kinda confusing right now watching John's interview on the Today show because last we talked, that pretty much was it,' Nikki told her sister. 'If I wanna be a mom, there's no John.'

While Brie agreed with Nikki, she also seemed hopeful that the couple would get back together.

'I just think that in that interview John could've went two different ways. He could've said, you know, 'This was a beautiful relationship. I learned a lot, but we're going our separate ways.' Or he could say what he did say,' Brie said.

Talk about it: The 34-year-old wrestler chatted with twin sister Brie about Cena's recent public appearances and her conflicting feelings about their relationship

Somber Cena: While Brie agreed with Nikki, she also seemed hopeful that the powerhouse couple would get back together

Earlier in the episode, Nikki feared her split from John would ruin the biggest moment of her wrestling career.

The episode titled The Bella Comeback showed Nikki preparing to make her big return to the ring at the first all-female Royal Rumble, which twin sister Brie Bella said was their chance to 'put our names in the history books.'

But Nikki was struggling not to be consumed by her split from John - especially when she saw him at the event without them speaking.

Historical event: Nikki Bella gave a toast after competing in the first all-female Royal Rumble on Sunday's episode of Total Bellas

Bold entrance: The 34-year-old wrestling star received thunderous applause upon her entrance to the Royal Rumble

'I feel like I've been on such an emotional rollercoaster and today has been like double that,' she said. 'It's so hard. I'm going to be a part of this major, historic moment, but I can't help but have all the John stuff on my mind.

'What our fans don't realize is we're human beings too and we go through struggles through our life. But when we walk out on that ramp we have to put the smile on our face ... the show still goes on,' Nikki said.

The event was also emotional for her family, with John seemingly snubbing and walking away from her brother J.J. and mom Kathy Colace, 53, when they called out to him backstage.

Broken up: John Cena was at the event but ignored his former fiancee Nikki and her family

That's awkward: Nikki was upset over her split with John but also was determined to put on a good show

'John not coming over and saying hi is a little awkward,' J.J. admitted later, sounding emotional.

'We're like brothers ... I'm not gonna say it hurts my feelings, but it gets me a little bummed out because we are so close.

'But this is all pretty raw and I don't know what state he's in right now.'

Bummed out: J.J. did not want to admit that his feelings were hurt when John snubbed him, but he did acknowledge being bummed out

Nikki's pain with the event started earlier when training took her home to Tampa, Florida, staying at their house for the first time since the split.

Despite insisting she did not feel 'anxiety' before going there, it clearly proved overwhelming for her - especially because she left her home keys in San Diego and had to call out Rob, John's best friend and personal trainer, to come and let her in.

Once inside, she admitted: 'Being here, in our home, it's giving me all of these emotions. I just see everything we've built here.'

Tough time: Nikki was struggling with being back at the Florida home that she shared with John

She was shown getting emotional after finding a card he left for her in the house, gushing about what it was like 'for me to watch you grow into something so beautiful and amazing.'

Asked if it was a sweet card, she smiled: 'The best.'

'It's really hard to be in this house without John,' she admitted. 'His presence is so strong here, so it's kind of hard to focus on Rumble.'

Nice card: John left a sweet card for Nikki at the house

Nikki was also worried about her serious neck injury, saying: 'My bone hasn't fused yet so pretty much everything is sticking together with two screws and a plate. It kind of messes with your mind.'

She admitted her doctor warned her about getting back in the ring, saying: 'For the rest of my life I will have issues with my neck.'

Brie, however, had other concerns - returning to the big stage after becoming a mom.

'Even though I'm really excited for the Royal Rumble, one thing really sticking out in my mind is that I don't really look like Brie Bella before I was pregnant,' she said.

'My whole career I've showed my stomach. I had ripped abs, I worked really hard for them. And then you give birth and you become a mom -- I'm really nervous because I feel like the fans won't recognize me because I can't show my stomach.'

'I just don't wanna go out there and people be like, ''Ugh, what is she doing here?''

Really nervous: Brie was nervous that her fans wouldn't recognize her without ripped abs

She was also shown grabbing her breasts backstage at the actual event, with her mom asking: 'Did you pump? I just don't want you to leak out there.'

They agreed the event was huge, with Brie saying: 'As women in WWE we have been waiting for a day like this for decades. So the fact that we actually get to stand here today and be a part of history -- that's incredible.'

Nikki told her sister: 'We've got a tired mama, we've got a broken heart, but no matter what we're going to go in there and kick some ass.'

Getting ready: Brie and Nikki trained together for the Royal Rumble

Wrestling stars: The twins have been WWE stars since 2007

Really tight: Nikki was tight while sparring with her sister

The Rumble featured multiple female stars of WWE with Maria Menounous hosting.

Nikki took the ring before Brie, with the fans going wild when she finally emerged and taking her mind off her heartbreak.

'This is the energy I'm so addicted to,' she said later. 'It's like an insane adrenaline rush. You can't even jump off the tallest mountain to feel what we feel in this ring.

Ring announcer: Maria Menounos was the ring announcer at the Royal Rumble

'It's like I just don't want this moment to end. Even though there are things going on in my life that make me so sad, I just try to remember these moments of, ''You got to be a part of history.''

Brie said her sister's 'big reaction' only added to her nerves, however, saying: 'I'm going to be among all the young hot girls and I don't wanna run out there looking like mom.'

Her fears were also wasted as the fans went equally as wild for her, with Brie saying later: 'This just makes me feel so good.... You had a baby, people think that's badass. And it is badass!

Fan favorite: Fans went wild for Brie when she entered the ring

'There's a lot of moms out there in the audience, and I want them to know -- just like my mom let me know -- it doesn't matter your age, it doesn't matter what you look like, you can have a badass comeback.'

The reaction clearly inspired Brie, as just three days later she posed for a photoshoot with her sister and a model in athletic underwear despite insisting she was 'embarrassed' by her body.

'I will never ever in my life allow any to photoshop my stretch marks because that right there is Birdie,' Brie insisted of her baby daughter.

Body confidence: The reception at Royal Rumble gave Brie some added body confidence

Sexy photoshoot: The sisters took part in another sexy photoshoot during the one-hour episode

Stomach showing: Brie as a new mother was proud of her body and took part in a lingerie shoot

'I'm gonna be proud of this body, and I want every mom to be proud too.'

Their mom, meanwhile, was finally about to get her own shot at her dream job as a broadcaster, something she gave up after having them.

She was shown nervously rehearsing for a possible job as a local weather reader, with son-in-law Bryan Danielson teasing her that she should 'market yourself as a sexy grandma bungling the weather.'

Weather girl: Nikki took over as weather girl as her mom Kathy Colace

Good job: Kathy later nailed her attempt at delivering the weather

She then seemed to botch her final interview, but finally getting it down at the end.

'I'm glad my mom didn't pick being a weather woman as a career because we'd all be living on the streets,' Brie joked, saying they were proud 'that she can still do it.'

'I give Ron Burgundy a lot of effing credit,' Nikki joked of Will Ferrell's newscaster from Anchorman, before Brie reminded her: 'He wasn't a weather man, though.'

A preview of next week's episode showed John telling Nikki that he still wanted to get married while she flatly said she wanted to be a mother.
